  "title": "Client Onboarding (Transition) Specialist (Contract)",
  "description": "<p>We are currently working with a global banking client to look for a <strong>Client Onboarding / Transition Specialist </strong>on a <u>contract </u>basis.</p><p>This role oversees the end-to-end onboarding of institutional clients across the APAC region, acting as the central coordinator from initial engagement through launch. The focus is on delivering a smooth, timely setup by aligning client needs with internal teams and systems.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Serve as the main client and sales contact throughout onboarding and launch.</li><li>Drive onboarding timelines by coordinating across KYC, Legal, Credit, Operations, IT, and e-Trading teams.</li><li>Gather and translate client requirements into executable delivery plans (accounts, trading access, reporting, documentation).</li><li>Track and prioritize onboarding activity across the regional pipeline.</li><li>Oversee approvals, system setup, testing, and readiness for go-live.</li><li>Support custom reporting requests and ongoing service enhancements.</li><li>Provide regular progress updates and management reporting to the business.</li><li>Partner with Sales and Client Services to strengthen client relationships and review service offerings.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements </strong></p><ul><li>4-7 years of experience within the capital / global markets space within banking and financial services.</li><li>Direct experience in client interaction, in addition to internal relationship management, and cross departmental communication.</li><li>Working with institutional clients / external stakeholders.</li><li>The candidate should possess excellent communication skills (both verbal and written).</li></ul>",
